data.title: Cape Cod, MA DX Audio Files from the Aurora of Mid
data.text:
Audio Files - South Yarmouth, Cape Cod, MA, USA - MAR 2015

(GC= 41.6931 N / 70.1912 W) (= 41° 41.59' N / 70° 11.47' W) (grid FN41vq)

(time and dates = UTC, year 2015)

Receiver: Microtelecom Perseus

Antenna-1: Cardioid pattern SuperLoop 10m vertical by 11m horizontal (peak 165 deg., null 345 deg.)

Antenna-2: Cardioid pattern SuperLoop 8m vertical by 15m horizontal (peak 75 deg., null 255 deg.)

similar antenna

photo of somewhat larger prior version of Antenna-1 (at same supports site)

Africa

1530 | SAO TOME E PRINCIPE | VOA, Pinheira, MAR 20 @ 0300 - Yankee Doodle music at sign-on; mixed with WCKY.

South America

540 | COLOMBIA | HJKA, Bogota, MAR 24 @ 0231 - Autentica mention in talk, hymn followed; mix with presumed Rebelde. Thanks to Horacio Nigro (RealDX list) for ID help.

540 | COLOMBIA | HJKA, Bogota, MAR 18 @ 0000 - Radio Autentica ID about 16 sec. into audio clip.

550 | COLOMBIA | HJHF, Señal Radio Colombia, Marinilla (Medellin), MAR 24 @ 0229 - Radio Colombia net ID; in jumble.

550 | COLOMBIA | HJHF, Señal Radio Colombia, Marinilla (Medellin), MAR 19 @ 0202 - // 570 HJND with Pomp & Circumstance march, Spanish talk; over WSJW-RI.

650 | COLOMBIA | HJKH, RCN Antena Dos, Bogota, MAR 19 @ 0200 - Antena Dos Colombia ID.

650 | COLOMBIA | HJKH, RCN Antena Dos, Bogota, MAR 20 @ 0001 - Antena Dos, Bogota ID; dominant.

690 | COLOMBIA | HJCZ, W Radio, Bogota, MAR 24 @ 0230 - "W Radio" ID; mixed with Cuba.

700 | COLOMBIA | HJCX, W Radio, Cali, MAR 22 @ 0300 - "W Radio" ID; dominant.

700.53 | VENEZUELA | YVMH, Maracaibo, MAR 20 @ 0330 - Radio Popular ID's, calliope / carnival type music; best on USB to dodge 700.0 HJCX.

720 | COLOMBIA | HJAN, Emisoras Unidas, Barranquilla, MAR 20 @ 0002 - Emisoras Unidas ID.

730 | COLOMBIA | HJCU, Cadena Melodia, Bogota, MAR 19 @ 0159 - Chimes, Bogota mention, Melodia Estereo ID's; good.

740 | VENEZUELA | YVNC, Maracaibo, MAR 22 @ 0259 - Union Radio network ID's; dominant.

750 | VENEZUELA | YVKS, RCR, Caracas, MAR 22 @ 0300 - RCR ID's; over Progreso Cuba.

760 | COLOMBIA | HJAJ, RCN, Barranquilla, MAR 20 @ 0000 - 5+1 time pips, RCN La Radio ID, Banco Popular mention, "RCN Noticias"; good.

770 | COLOMBIA | HJJX, RCN, Bogota, MAR 20 @ 0000 - Time pips then RCN La Radio, Banco Popular, and RCN Noticias mentions; over Cuba, others.

780 | VENEZUELA | YVMN, R. Coro, Coro, MAR 20 @ 0329 - ID "Somos AM, Radio Coro, siete ochenta, patrimonio de la comunidad."; dominant.

810 | COLOMBIA | HJCY, CARACOL, Bogota, MAR 20 @ 0301 - CARACOL Radio ID; over Bahamas.

850 | COLOMBIA | HJKC, R. Candela, Bogota, MAR 20 @ 0001 - Radio Candela ID's in mix with WEEI. Thanks to Chuck Hutton and Horacio Nigro (RealDX list) for ID help.

900 | VENEZUELA | YVMD, Maracaibo, MAR 19 @ 0201 - Several "en Venezuela" mentions; over others.

980 | COLOMBIA | HJES, Cali, MAR 24 @ 0002 - "RCN Noticias" mention; mixed with Reloj Cuba.

1000 | VENEZUELA | YVNM, R.Caribena, Moron, MAR 24 @ 0228 - Radio Caribena ID; poor.

1010 | COLOMBIA (t) | HJCC, Bogota, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Spanish talk; way under WINS. Per Fredrik Douren on RealDX "I can recognize the voice and I think there is a Acuario at 8 sec. so I'm pretty sure it is Bogota."

1040 | COLOMBIA (t) | ?, MAR 24 @ 0001 - Apparent Radio Colombia network ID; poor.

1070 | COLOMBIA | HJCG, R. Santa Fe, Bogota, MAR 20 @ 0300 - Q'hubo Radio and Radio Santa Fe ID's; dominant.

1070 | COLOMBIA | HJCG, R. Santa Fe, Bogota, MAR 24 @ 0001 - Q'hubo Radio jingle/ID, Radio Santa Fe ID; to good peak.

1100 | COLOMBIA | HJCN, Bogota, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Religious-format Spanish speaker. Central American places mentioned. Not usual HJAT. Chuck Hutton (RealDX) "At 1 min. 40 sec. there's a BBN ID. The references to Honduras and Guatemala are not local references. No doubt it is Bogota." Fredrik Douren (RealDX): "It's BBN, the only one I know on 1100 is Bogota, Colombia."

1110 | VENEZUELA | YVQT, R. Carupano, Carupano, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Electronic sound, ID "Esta es Radio Carupano"; to fair peak.

1170 | COLOMBIA | HJNW, CARACOL, Cartagena, MAR 20 @ 0000 - CARACOL Radio ID; fair, dominant.

1190 | COLOMBIA | HJCV, R. Cordillera, Bogota, MAR 23 @ 2359 - ID "Desde Bogota, Radio Cordillera"; over WLIB.

1290 | VENEZUELA | YVLF, R. Puerto Cabello, Puerto Cabello, MAR 22 @ 0159 - Radio Puerto Cabello ID; over WRNI-RI.

1520 | COLOMBIA | HJLI, R. Libertad, Bogota, MAR 22 @ 0100 - Libertad and Bogota mentions in Spanish religious programming; dominant.

Recording of 3 Colombian Señal Radio Colombia outlets.

MAR 24 @ 0230 UTC: 680, 550, and 570 as below: accordion music and male vocal

680 HJBU, Zambrano: 0 (start) to 10 sec.: way under WRKO

550 HJHF, Marinilla (Medellin): 10 to 25 sec.: dominant

570 HJND, Bogota (El Rosal): 25 sec. to 37 sec. (end): under Reloj Cuba

Central America and Mexico

539.86 | NICARAGUA | YNOW, R. Corporacion, Managua, MAR 20 @ 0301 - Radio Corporacion and "en Managua" mentions; fair on LSB to dodge 540 stations (WFLF, HJKA, Rebelde).

720 | NICARAGUA | R. Catolica, Managua, MAR 18 @ 0200 - Bells, ID "Radio Catolica de Nicaragua".

860 | PANAMA | HOL55, R. Reforma, Chitre, MAR 22 @ 0301 - Radio Reforma ID, talk, and accordion music; over Reloj Cuban.

1140 | MEXICO (t) | XEMR, Monterrey, MAR 24 @ 0229 - Possible ID about 6 sec. into audio clip. Per Bruce Conti (RealDX): "Sounds like 'desde Monterrey' and the type of programming (at least as far as I can tell from such a short audio clip) that would be on XEMR."

Caribbean excluding Cuba

580 | PUERTO RICO | WKAQ, San Juan, MAR 20 @ 0000 - WKAQ ID's, mention of electoral year; huge.

580 | PUERTO RICO | WKAQ, San Juan, MAR 24 @ 0228 - WKAQ Cinco Ochenta ID; good, over Rebelde Cuba.

600 | PUERTO RICO | WYEL, Mayaguez, MAR 24 @ 0000 - // 580 WKAQ with fast talk and Puerto Rico mention; under Rebelde Cuba.

630 | PUERTO RICO | WUNO, NotiUno, San Juan, MAR 20 @ 0000 - List of network affiliates, "NotiUno en la noche" slogan; loud, dominant.

630 | PUERTO RICO | WUNO, NotiUno, San Juan, MAR 24 @ 0230 - "NotiUno, primer en las noticias", "escuche NotiUno 630"; good, over Cuba and WPRO.

680 | PUERTO RICO | WAPA, San Juan, MAR 24 @ 0001 - La Poderosa slogan, San Juan mention, list of network affiliates; under WRKO.

760 | PUERTO RICO | WORA, Mayaguez, MAR 24 @ 0001 - NotiUno net ID (// 630 WUNO); under RCN Colombia.

780 | BRITISH VIRGIN ISLANDS | ZBVI, Road Town, Tortola, MAR 18 @ 0201 - Man mentioned Tortola, then woman "ZBVI now concludes its broadcasting day." Hymn at sign-off possibly by '50s country singer Jim Reeves. Only fair strength but dominant.

800 | BONAIRE | PJB, TransWorld Radio, Kralendijk, MAR 20 @ 0330 - Man with Radio Transmundial ID and mentions of Bonaire, Antillas Holandesas; good.

810 | BAHAMAS | ZNS3, Freeport, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Locally-accented phone-in show with talk about Bahamian boxer Elisha Obed; over HJCY and Progreso Cuba

830 | DOMINICAN REPUBLIC | HIJB, Santo Domingo, MAR 24 @ 0231 - Man in Spanish with noticias and HIJB mentions; mixed with WCRN.

860 | ST. KITTS & NEVIS | V. of Nevis, Bath Village, MAR 18 @ 0200 - The powerhouse of the eastern Caribbean, VON Radio from the Federation of St. Kitts and Nevis.; fair, dominant.

860 | ST. KITTS & NEVIS | V. of Nevis, Bath Village, MAR 19 @ 0200 - Clear ID "With all the power from the tower, this is the powerhouse of the eastern Caribbean, VON Radio from the Federation of St. Kitts and Nevis."

940 | PUERTO RICO | WIPR, Maxima 940, San Juan, MAR 24 @ 0001 - ID "en San Juan, Maxima, Nueve Cuarenta"; over Cuba.

1120 | PUERTO RICO | WMSW, R. Once, Hatillo, MAR 24 @ 0000 - ID's "WMSW .. Hatillo, Puerto Rico .. Radio Once"; dominant.

1160 | ANTIGUA | Caribbean Radio Lighthouse, St. John's, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Caribbean Radio Lighthouse ID, hymn; over unID Spanish, WOBM, others.

1280 | PUERTO RICO | WCMN, Arecibo, MAR 24 @ 0001 - List of network affiliates in Mayaguez, Arecibo, et al., NotiUno jingle and net ID; over jumble (Brazil, Bermuda, WADO, others).

1610 | ANGUILLA | Caribbean Beacon, The Valley, MAR 22 @ 0300 - usual "You're watching the University Network" mention, then preaching; dominant over low-pitched growls from TIS / HAR stations.

Cuba - Rebelde network

530 | CUBA | R. Rebelde, Guantanamo, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; mixed with classical music from Radio Enciclopedia.

560 | CUBA | R. Rebelde, Ciego Avila, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; mixed with WGAN-ME.

600 | CUBA | CMKV, R. Rebelde, Urbano Noris, MAR 24 @ 0000 - // 670 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; over WYEL Puerto Rico.

620 | CUBA | R. Rebelde, Colon / Moa, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; dominant.

670 | CUBA | CMQ, R. Rebelde, Arroyo Arenas, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 770 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; dominant.

710 | CUBA | R. Rebelde synchros, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with "Deportivamente" promo, organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; loud.

770 | CUBA | R. Rebelde, Victoria de las Tunas, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with "Deportivamente" promo, organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; loud.

1180 | CUBA | R. Rebelde synchros, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; loud, two outlets had about a second audio delay between them.

1210 | CUBA | R. Rebelde, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Organ music and Rebelde ID; under WPHT.

1550 | CUBA | R. Rebelde synchros, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Rebelde la Habana ID.

1620 | CUBA | R. Rebelde synchros, MAR 24 @ 0230 - // 670 et al. with organ music, man with ID "Rebelde, la Habana, emisora de la revolucion"; some echo noticed.

Cuba - Reloj network

790 | CUBA | R. Reloj, Pinar del Rio & Holguin, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Radio Reloj ID by woman and "RR" beeps, two stations in network with about a half second delay between. Over second Spanish speaking station as well as WPRV-RI and WAXY-FL.

850 | CUBA | R. Reloj, Nueva Gerona, MAR 24 @ 0231 - Talk, "RR" beeps through WEEI/WFTL mix.

860 | CUBA | R. Reloj, Jovellanos, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Ocho de la noche ... transmite Radio Reloj desde la Habana, Cuba; dominant.

870 | CUBA | R. Reloj synchros, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Woman with "diez con treinte minutos" timecheck and Radio Reloj ID; good.

870 | CUBA | R. Reloj synchros, MAR 20 @ 0300 - Single beep, man with "once de la noche" timecheck and "Transmite Radio Reloj desde la Habana, Cuba" ID; dominant.

930 | CUBA | R. Reloj synchros, MAR 24 @ 0231 - Reloj programming; under WPKX-NH.

950 | CUBA | R. Reloj, La Habana & Mayari Arriba, MAR 24 @ 0231 - Woman "Radio Reloj ... diez treinte y uno minutos"; loud, dominant.

960 | CUBA | R. Reloj, Guantanamo, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Woman "Radio Reloj ... diez y treinte minutos ... Habana, Cuba"; fair to good.

980 | CUBA | R. Reloj, Moa, MAR 24 @ 0230 - "Reloj .. desde la Habana, Cuba"; over jumble.

Cuba - Radio Progreso network

940 | CUBA | R. Progreso, Sancti Spiritus, MAR 24 @ 0001 - Flute music // other Progreso outlets; under WIPR Puerto Rico.

Recording of Cuban Radio Progreso outlets .

MAR 20 @ 0331 UTC, frequencies as noted below: Frank Sinatra "Forget Domani" song

900: 0 (start) to 22 sec.: huge

890: 22 to 31 sec.: over others

630: 31 to 37 sec.: mix WPRO-RI

640: 37 to 45 sec.: dominant

650: 45 to 55 sec.: over 660 WFAN slop

690: 55 sec. to 1 min. 2 sec.: good

720: 1 min. 2 sec. to 1 min. 9 sec.: poor to fair, dominant

730: 1 min. 9 sec. to 1 min. 15 sec.: fair, dominant

750: 1 min. 15 sec. to 1 min. 22 sec. (end): good

Cuba - miscellaneous

530 | CUBA | CMBQ, R. Enciclopedia, La Habana, MAR 20 @ 0300 - Woman with "Radio Enciclopedia desde la Habana, Cuba" ID.

740 | CUBA | R. Angulo, Sagua de Tanamo, MAR 20 @ 0000 - ID "Radio Angulo .. en Cuba", chimes, jingle; good over others.

840 | CUBA | CMHW, "W", Santa Clara, MAR 20 @ 0300 - Man with ID "Esta es Dobleve, desde Santa Clara, en el centro de Cuba"; loud / dominant.

910 | CUBA | R. Cadena Agramonte, Camaguey, MAR 20 @ 0302 - Radio Cadena Agramonte ID; fair, somewhat noisy.

910 | CUBA | R. Cadena Agramonte, Camaguey, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Music, ID by man "Radio Cadena Agramonte, Camaguey, Cuba"; good.

1000 | CUBA | R. Granma, Media Luna, MAR 26 @ 0101 - Woman with "Radio Granma" ID, chimes; poor but dominant.

1020 | CUBA | ?, MAR 24 @ 0001 - Talk seems to be Cuba and "revolucion" related but a different station from the co-channel Reloj signal in the background. Per Chuck Hutton (RealDX) "Clearly Cuba but no program name or local mention."

1020 | CUBA | R. Artemisa, MAR 24 @ 0231 - Two unID's competing (weaker station using reverb) then Reloj Cuba sneaks in. Per Mauricio Molano (RealDX) "Radio Artemisa (ID) at 53 sec."

1060 | CUBA | R. 26, Jovellanos, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Radio Veintiseis (26) ID; over WQOM/KYW.

1110 | CUBA | R. Angulo, MAR 24 @ 0001 - Radio Angulo ID; poor but dominant.

1140 | CUBA | R. Surco, Moron, MAR 24 @ 0000 - ID "Transmite CMIP, Radio Surco, desde Ciego de Avila, capital de la locucion cubana."; fair, dominant.

1150 | CUBA | R. Bayamo, Bueycito, MAR 24 @ 0232 - Radio Bayamo ID; dominant.

1210 | CUBA | R. Sancti Spiritus, MAR 23 @ 2359 - Two stations. One is Rebelde Cuba. Second one has chimes around 20 sec. and talk that might be ID material. Per Bruce Conti (RealDX): "The chimes belong to Radio Sancti Spiritus (Cuba)."

1350 | CUBA | ?, MAR 22 @ 0300 - Cuban national anthem.

unidentified Latin American

740 | unID | ?, MAR 24 @ 0230 - Spanish talk; under slightly wobbly R. Angulo, Cuba.

USA

540 WFLF FL, Pine Hills - Orlando, MAR 18 @ 0200 - End of "Brain Health" infomercial medical show, ID "WFLF Pine Hills - Orlando, WMGF HD3 Mt. Dora - Orlando", into Fox news; good.

610 WIOD FL, Miami, MAR 20 @ 0000 - Miami traffic, "News Radio 610 WIOD" ID, weather; good.

640 WMEN FL, Royal Palm Beach, MAR 20 @ 0000 - Man "in Royal Palm Beach - Miami", ABC sports update; over Progreso Cuba.

670 WWFE FL, Miami, MAR 18 @ 0200 - Spanish talk with Poderosa slogan and "en Miami"; slightly over Rebelde Cuba.

710 WAQI FL, Miami, MAR 20 @ 0001 - Spanish talk, "Mambi" jingle under Cuba, no WOR

740 WSBR FL, Boca Raton, MAR 19 @ 2359 - "South Florida's Money Talk Radio ... WSBR"; fair.

790 WAXY FL, Miami, MAR 18 @ 0200 - Fort Lauderdale Auto Show advert, WAXY ID; over WPRV-RI and Reloj Cuba.

850 WFTL FL, West Palm Beach, MAR 24 @ 0000 - ID "This is 850 WFTL West Palm Beach - Fort Lauderdale - Miami" noted right after ID of equal-strength WEEI Boston.

900 WSWN FL, Belle Glade, MAR 24 @ 0000 - Promo for ' http://www.900thetalk.com/ ' website; under huge Progreso Cuba.

1260 WSUA FL, Miami, MAR 22 @ 0301 - Spanish talk with WSUA and Caracol ID's.

1320 WLQY FL, Hollywood, MAR 22 @ 0300 - WLQY ID; dominant.

1370 WTAB NC, Tabor City, MAR 22 @ 0300 - ID "We're AM 1370 WTAB".

1580 WZKY NC, Albemarle, MAR 22 @ 0300 - Aretha Franklin song, "Oldies Radio WZKY" jingle.

1700 WJCC FL, Miami Springs, MAR 22 @ 0300 - Disclaimer "The views expressed in this program do not necessarily reflect those of Radio Mega LLC or AM 1700 WJCC", mention of covering Palm Beach area and northern Haiti.
